main event: Two star-shaped objects were observed in the sky over Alexandria, Louisiana on September 7, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were described as being the size of a pencil eraser held at arm's length., Both objects emitted a bright white light., The first object was visible for 2 minutes, while the second was visible for 3 minutes., The observers relied on ground visual observation and the use of binoculars., Weather conditions at the time were clear with unlimited ceiling and 10 miles visibility.
witness description: Individuals with above-average reliability who observed the objects from their yard.
